ADDITIONAL NOTICE — AUTHORIZED USE ONLY

EagleEye is a defensive security and network-analysis tool. It is intended
solely for use on networks that the operator owns or for which the operator
has explicit, written authorization to audit.

Unauthorized scanning, monitoring, or analysis of networks or devices that
you do not own or are not authorized to test may violate applicable law,
including but not limited to:

  - Article 370B / 370C of the Greek Criminal Code (Παράνομη πρόσβαση σε
    σύστημα πληροφοριών, παραβίαση δεδομένων προσωπικού χαρακτήρα)
  - Regulation (EU) 2016/679 (GDPR) and Greek Law 4624/2019
  - Directive 2002/58/EC (ePrivacy) and Greek Law 3471/2006
  - The Convention on Cybercrime (Budapest, 2001)
  - Computer Fraud and Abuse Act (18 U.S.C. § 1030) in U.S. jurisdictions
  - Equivalent statutes in other jurisdictions

The authors and contributors of this software accept no responsibility for
unlawful or unauthorized use. By using EagleEye you accept full responsibility
for ensuring your use complies with all applicable laws and that you have
proper authorization for every network you audit.
